column5: I had Sunday morning free. Late Saturday night I still couldn't decide what species to target or what lake to visit. There's so many options this time of year.  I went for skis. It was a one follow, one strike, one fish morning.    I could have been better, it could have been worse too.    I did find an old memory card with some trail camera pics at the cottage.  Cute little bugger that could probably rip your hand off pretty quickly.       Uh oh, I wasn't really looking for you.     All seasons are great up there, but this time of the year is awesome.
Agreed! Love this time of year! Nice ski!
Nice colourful back ground. Yes, it,s that time of year.  Nice fish Chris.
Beautiful ski chris! Ill be up there next week i hope i can get into some too! Thats a pretty good sized bear too lol

Good one Chris, real purdy fish.  But I was just scrolling thru the pictures at 1st without reading the text and came across the critter in the snow and couldn't believe you got all that white stuff last night when I'm not too far south and we're sitting here sunny & warm
Nice ski...keep baiting that bear for me until next September...id like to sausage-ize him
Anglers are good.  Fishers are evil.
Nice pics and sweet muskellunge!!!  And you are absolutely correct, this time of year IS awesome!!!
Great fish and pics of the critters u have a piece of paradise there as well
Nice close-up of the fisher (at least it looks like one to me).  what were you fishing out of? your knees are well above the gunnels there.

Nice ski...keep baiting that bear for me until next September...id like to sausage-ize him  nooooooo, I want him to go away because he likes to fragment-ize my BBQ   Nice close-up of the fisher (at least it looks like one to me).  what were you fishing out of? your knees are well above the gunnels there.  it's a fisher  a 14' tinny, a long day in that thing kills my knees and hips, getting old
Nice fish - which is better than no fish...
Fishing reports are the best part of this site. Thanks for sharing!
